				<li id="16663826" class="cmnt-root" data="94" data-d="1651490049000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578914/Meteoric-Ore-Blade" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">02 May 2022 07:14</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16663826" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Looking solely at my PvP experience, I&apos;d argue that this weapon outperforms Moonveil by a significant margin just due to the fact that most people ignore it.<br/><br/>Moonveil is a caster&apos;s wet dream. High scaling, powerful WA, braindeath required for use. Not that hard to use, but by now everyone and their mother knows the timings to avoid, counter, or parry it. It scales off of two of the preferred stats for magic; damage and speed. It&apos;s a weapon that has gained memetic status as a choice melee tool for casters just due to how absolutely simple it is to use, yet effective for that simplicity. But as mentioned, this means that everyone and their mother knows how to counter it.<br/><br/>Meanwhile this thing just fricken&apos; slaps. The WA may seem weak or unimpressive, but it catches rolls like a fat man in a bakery and then drags &apos;em in close for the absolute most chad R2 in the game, a basic (but absolutely damaging and poise smashing) helm splitter. Nobody is joking when they say that thing is practically a WA in and of itself. With the abilities this katana has, and it&apos;s relative obscurity to most of the casual community, this thing functions as one hell of a weapon to use against invaders or duelists because, simply put, nobody is prepared for it.<br/><br/>Overall, I&apos;m running a magic swordsman build that uses both (with this as the primary hand and the Moonveil as offhand), but this weapon in particular comes out when invaders come knocking. Wanna run? Better ask the Meteoric Ore Blade if you&apos;re allowed.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16663826" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16663826" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">4</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>97</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>3</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16663826"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16663826" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16663826"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
